{"TopicId":190165,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"IVA Camera Tool","CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-03T20:00:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-03T20:00:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnybody have a iva camera tool. I want to do interior shots (In the cockpit.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-04T13:15:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreetings, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201477-arco123/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022201477\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201477-arco123/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Arco123\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve split your question off to its own thread in the proper subforum for this type of question.\u00A0 The thread you posted in is meant for little questions about real-life spaceflight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood luck with your quest \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-04T15:26:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"themaster401","CreatedById":155752,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-04T15:55:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor IVA shots, I typically use\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184142-ksp-18x-cameratools-v1130-28-oct-2019/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ECameraTools\u0027\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0pathing function, enable the IVA overlay in Flight view, and adjust the camera to any position and pan I wish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-04T23:32:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223713310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575474951\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022themaster401\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, themaster401 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor IVA shots, I typically use\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184142-ksp-18x-cameratools-v1130-28-oct-2019/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ECameraTools\u0027\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0pathing function, enable the IVA overlay in Flight view, and adjust the camera to any position and pan I wish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*HEAD EXPLODES*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike, not f\u0027ing kidding I never ever thought of that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add on to that suggestion though, also make use of Scatterer and enable its near-clip plane override setting. Set it to something like 0.01 and you can move the camera a lot closer to objects before they \u0022clip\u0022 and you start seeing through walls and kerbal heads\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-06T14:59:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease, step by step. I\u0027m way too new.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I do have it. (Camera tools)\u00A0I just don\u0027t know how to do it... Note some keys or steps to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-06T15:01:31Z\u0022 title=\u002212/06/2019 03:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 6, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Arco123\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-31T15:52:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223713447\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575502327\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Drew Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/4/2019 at 6:32 PM, Drew Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*HEAD EXPLODES*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike, not f\u0027ing kidding I never ever thought of that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add on to that suggestion though, also make use of Scatterer and enable its near-clip plane override setting. Set it to something like 0.01 and you can move the camera a lot closer to objects before they \u0022clip\u0022 and you start seeing through walls and kerbal heads\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103177-drew-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022103177\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103177-drew-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Drew Kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I did it but it still clipped through pretty fast. \u00A0I know the setting but which way increases\u00A0and decreases because\u00A0there\u0027s no change in the clip range.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-01T00:41:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223723041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221577807559\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Arco123\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Arco123 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103177-drew-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022103177\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/103177-drew-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Drew Kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I did it but it still clipped through pretty fast. \u00A0I know the setting but which way increases\u00A0and decreases because\u00A0there\u0027s no change in the clip range.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlay around with values,, make\u00A0sure it\u2019s properly enabled. If you still don\u2019t notice anything post in the a Scatterer thread. It was an option that was removed but then re-added, it may be working differently now, but I know it used to do that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-01T00:44:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried again but it seems to not affect it. It says restart on disable which I don\u0027t know what that means but it only does just that range regardless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-15T01:47:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201477-arco123/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022201477\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/201477-arco123/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Arco123\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I use hullcamVDS and clip the cameras into the cockpit.\u00A0 Takes a while to set up but then I\u0027m always going to get the same shots.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeace.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}